  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency food assistance for drought-affected households and communities, to enhance resilience to shocks</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The key objective of this project is to protect the livelihoods of drought-affected vulnerable households and agro-pastoral and pastoral communities in the Northern Red Sea, Southern Red Sea, and Anseba regions and enhance resilience to shocks. This UNDP project includes the provision of lifesaving food assistance through food for work, unconditional food assistance for people with disability and vulnerable women headed households, and provision of essential household items. The project provides humanitarian assistance to 21,600 people, including 6,221 women, 3,034 men,  12,345 children, and 1,288 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
